Detailed Description

A complex Request object.

The Request is built up of a collection of Packets and intelligence to create the different Packets.

New requests must inherit from RequestWithStatus instead of Request.

virtual PacketContainer* Request::getNextPacket (   )  [virtual]
 

Return the next Packet with no unresolved datadependencies from the list of packets ready to send in m_packetsReadyToSend.

Subclasses may, but doesn't need to, override this method. The default implementation here is to return a packet from m_packetsReadyToSend.

Returns:
Packet if available, NULL otherwise

Reimplemented in ACPTileMapRequest, AddUserTrackRequest, AllUserRequest, MC2BoundingBoxRequest, CoordinateObject, CoordinateOnItemRequest, ExpandRouteRequest, GetUserTrackRequest, ItemInfoRequest, LocalMapMessageRequest, MapRequest, MultiplePacketsRequest, ProximityRequest, RouteMessageRequest, RouteRequest, SinglePacketRequest, SMSSendRequest, SortDistRequest, StringTableRequest, and UserFavoritesRequest.
